    <note>Sun(1) Yong [1555] Chong's [1513] grandson. His father, Dan [3783], died young. At the age of 10, Yong used his grandfather's yin for a nominal appointment in the civil service. A son-in-law, Yan(1) Ruocai [4081, was almost certainly related to Yan(1) Ruogu [2059] (qv.) and Yan(1) Ruomeng [2060], but all efforts have failed to yield an address for them. XCB, 255.10a, 284.17a, 295.9a; SHY:ZG, 65.30a; Su Song, WJ, 53.1a-14a; YLDD, 12506.11b. CBD, 3, 1880-1.</note>
